# RPG Game with Ursina Engine

This repository contains the source code for an RPG game developed using the Ursina game engine. The game features player movement, inventory management, and interactive items.

## Requirements

- [Ursina Engine](https://www.ursinaengine.org/): A beginner-friendly game engine for creating 2D and 3D games in Python.

## Getting Started

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:
git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/RPG-Game.git

    Install the Ursina engine if you haven't already:
pip install ursina

    Run the game:
python main.py

    Use your gamepad to control the character and interact with the environment.

Gameplay Features

    Player movement using a gamepad controller.
    Interactive items: Swords, shields, and health potions that you can pick up.
    Inventory management: View and equip items in your inventory.
    Pause Menu: Press the 'Start' button to access the pause menu.
    Health bar: Monitor your character's health.

Controls

    Left stick: Move the character.
    Right stick: Control the camera.
    A button: Jump.
    Y button: Interact with items.

Customization

Feel free to customize and extend the game to add more features, levels, or characters. You can also improve the graphics, animations, and gameplay mechanics.
Acknowledgments

    This game was developed using the Ursina game engine.
    Some 3D models used in the game are courtesy of online 3D model repositories
